#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:3
msgid ""
"These are the instructions if you just want to follow the latest *NumPy* "
"source, but you don't need to do any development for now. If you do want to "
"contribute a patch (excellent!) or do more extensive NumPy development, see :"
"ref:`development-workflow`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:8
msgid "The steps are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:10
msgid ":ref:`install-git`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:11
msgid "get local copy of the git repository from Github_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:12
msgid "update local copy from time to time"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:15
msgid "Get the local copy of the code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:17
msgid "From the command line::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:19
#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:24
msgid "git clone https://github.com/numpy/numpy.git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:21
msgid ""
"You now have a copy of the code tree in the new ``numpy`` directory. If this "
"doesn't work you can try the alternative read-only url::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:27
msgid "Updating the code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:29
msgid ""
"From time to time you may want to pull down the latest code.  Do this with::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:31
msgid ""
"cd numpy\n"
"git fetch\n"
"git merge --ff-only"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../dev/gitwash/following_latest.rst:35
msgid ""
"The tree in ``numpy`` will now have the latest changes from the initial "
"repository."
msgstr ""
